{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891867089,"sessionID":"ses_28498b584ffeqx648sCyueA5sT","part":{"id":"prt_d7b676585001ylQH6dVlTOUd4q","messageID":"msg_d7b674b6a001AvRzUBS9KeQB1Z","sessionID":"ses_28498b584ffeqx648sCyueA5sT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0c3021ba44f1467bb5d940e026a865a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write proposal.md for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n4: Module: integrations\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: Relevant specs:\n9: --- integrations/design.md ---\n10: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n11: \n12: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n13: \n14: ## Dify plugin — file map\n15: \n16: | File | Role |\n17: |------|------|\n18: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n19: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n20: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n21: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n22: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n23: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n24: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n25: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n26: \n27: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n28: \n29: From source:\n30: \n31: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n32: - `type`: `plugin`\n33: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n34: - `name`: `agentcube`\n35: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n36: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n37: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n38: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n39: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n40: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n41: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n42: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n43: \n44: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n45: \n46: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n47: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n48: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n49: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n50: \n51: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n52: \n53: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n54: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n55: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n56: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n57: \n58: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n59: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n60: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n61: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n62: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n63: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n64: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n65: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n66: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n67: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n68: \n69: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n70: \n71: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n75: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n76: \n77: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n78:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n79:         try:\n80:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n81:         except Exception as e:\n82:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n83: ```\n84: \n85: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n86: \n87: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n88: \n89: ```python\n90: from collections.abc import Generator\n91: from typing import Any\n92: from dify_plugin import Tool\n93: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n94: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n95: \n96: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n97:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n98:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n99:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n100: \n101:     def execute(\n102:         self,\n103:         router_url=None,\n104:         workload_manager_url=None,\n105:         language=\"python\",\n106:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n107:         session_id=None,\n108:         code=None,\n109:         command=None,\n110:         session_reuse=False,\n111:         **kwargs\n112:     ): ...\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n116: \n117: ```\n118: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n119: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n123: \n124: | File | Role |\n125: |------|------|\n126: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n127: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n128: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n129: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n130: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n131: \n132: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n133: \n134: ### Globals / config (selected)\n135: \n136: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n137: |------|--------|-----------------|\n138: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n139: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n140: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n141: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n142: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n143: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n144: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n145: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n146: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n147: \n148: ### Core classes / functions\n149: \n150: ```python\n151: class SandboxRunner:\n152:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n153:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n154:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n155:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n156:     def stop(self): ...\n157: \n158: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n159: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n160: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n161: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n162: \n163: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n164: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n165: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n166: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n168: \n169: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n170:     script: str\n171:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n172:     report: str\n173: \n174: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### FastAPI endpoints\n178: \n179: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n180: |--------|------|----------------------|\n181: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n182: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n183: \n184: ### Imports of note\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n188: from pydantic import BaseModel\n189: import uvicorn\n190: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n191: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n192: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n193: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n194: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n198: \n199: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n200: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n201: - Container port `8000` TCP\n202: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n203: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n204: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n205: \n206: ## Dockerfile highlights\n207: \n208: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n209: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n210: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n211: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n212: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n213: \n214: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n215: \n216: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n217: \n218: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n219: \n220: \n221: --- integrations/spec.md ---\n222: # Integrations Specification\n223: \n224: ## Purpose\n225: \n226: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n227: \n228: ## Requirements\n229: \n230: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n231: \n232: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n235: \n236: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n237: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n238: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n243: \n244: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n249: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n250: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n253: \n254: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n255: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n256: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n261: \n262: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n267: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n268: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n273: \n274: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n279: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n280: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n285: \n286: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n289: \n290: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n291: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n292: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n295: \n296: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n297: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n298: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n303: \n304: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n307: \n308: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n309: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n310: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n315: \n316: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n319: \n320: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n321: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n322: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n327: \n328: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n331: \n332: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n333: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n334: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n339: \n340: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n343: \n344: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n345: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n346: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n349: \n350: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n351: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n352: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n357: \n358: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n361: \n362: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n363: - **WHEN** the service starts\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n369: \n370: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n375: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n376: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n379: \n380: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n381: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n382: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n383: \n384: ---\n385: \n386: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n387: \n388: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n391: \n392: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n393: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n394: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n399: \n400: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n401: \n402: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n403: \n404: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n405: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n406: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n409: \n410: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n411: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n412: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n413: \n414: \n415: --- python-sdk/design.md ---\n416: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n417: \n418: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n419: \n420: ## Package layout\n421: \n422: | Path | Role |\n423: |------|------|\n424: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n425: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n426: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n427: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n428: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n429: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n430: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n431: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n432: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n433: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n434: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n435: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n436: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n437: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n438: \n439: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n440: \n441: ```python\n442: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n443: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n444: \n445: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n446: ```\n447: \n448: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n449: \n450: ```python\n451: __all__ = [\n452:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n453:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n454:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n455: ]\n456: ```\n457: \n458: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n459: \n460: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n461: \n462: | Component | Resolved settings |\n463: |-----------|-------------------|\n464: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n465: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n466: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n467: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n468: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n469: \n470: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n471: \n472: ```python\n473: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n474:     def __init__(\n475:         self,\n476:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n477:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n478:         ttl: int = 3600,\n479:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n480:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n481:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n482:         verbose: bool = False,\n483:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n484:     ): ...\n485: \n486:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n487: \n488:     def __enter__(self): ...\n489:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n490: \n491:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n492: \n493:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n494:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n495:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n496:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n497:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n498:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n499: ```\n500: \n501: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n502: \n503: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n504: \n505: ```python\n506: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n507:     def __init__(\n508:         self,\n509:         agent_name: str,\n510:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n511:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n512:         verbose: bool = False,\n513:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n514:         timeout: int = 120,\n515:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n516:     ): ...\n517: \n518:     def __enter__(self): ...\n519:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n520: \n521:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n522: \n523:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n524: ```\n525: \n526: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n527: \n528: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n529: \n530: ```python\n531: class ControlPlaneClient:\n532:     def __init__(\n533:         self,\n534:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n535:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n536:         timeout: int = 120,\n537:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n538:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n539:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n540:     ): ...\n541: \n542:     def create_session(\n543:         self,\n544:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n545:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n546:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n547:         ttl: int = 3600,\n548:     ) -> str: ...\n549: \n550:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n551: \n552:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n553: ```\n554: \n555: ### Control plane — HTTP\n556: \n557: | Method | Path | Notes |\n558: |--------|------|-------|\n559: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n560: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n561: \n562: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n563: \n564: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n565: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n566: \n567: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n568: \n569: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n570: \n571: ```python\n572: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n573:     def __init__(\n574:         self,\n575:         session_id: str,\n576:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n577:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n578:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n579:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n580:         timeout: int = 120,\n581:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n582:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n583:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n584:     ): ...\n585: \n586:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n587: \n588:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n589:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n590:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n591:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n592:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n593:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n594:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n598: \n599: If `base_url` is not provided:\n600: \n601: ```text\n602: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n603: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n604: ```\n605: \n606: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n607: \n608: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n609: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n610: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n611: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n612: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n613: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n614: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n615: \n616: **Headers:**\n617: \n618: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n619: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n620: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n621: \n622: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n623: \n624: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n625: \n626: ```python\n627: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n628:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n629: \n630:     def __init__(\n631:         self,\n632:         router_url: str,\n633:         namespace: str,\n634:         agent_name: str,\n635:         timeout: int = 120,\n636:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n637:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n638:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n639:     ): ...\n640: \n641:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n642: \n643:     def invoke(\n644:         self,\n645:         session_id: str,\n646:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n647:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n648:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n649: \n650:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n651: ```\n652: \n653: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n654: \n655: ```text\n656: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n657: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ### Data plane — HTTP\n661: \n662: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n663: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n664: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n665: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n666: \n667: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n668: \n669: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n670: \n671: ```python\n672: def create_session(\n673:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n674:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n675: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n676: ```\n677: \n678: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n679: \n680: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n681: \n682: ```python\n683: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n684: ```\n685: \n686: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n687: \n688: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n689: \n690: ```python\n691: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n692: ```\n693: \n694: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n695: \n696: ```python\n697: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n698:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n699:     pass\n700: \n701: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n702:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n703:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n704:         self.stderr = stderr\n705:         self.command = command\n706:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n707: \n708: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n709:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n710:     pass\n711: \n712: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n713:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n714:     pass\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n718: \n719: ```toml\n720: dependencies = [\n721:     \"requests\",\n722:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n723:     \"cryptography\",\n724: ]\n725: ```\n726: \n727: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n728: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n729: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n730: \n731: \n732: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n733: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n734: \n735: ## Purpose\n736: \n737: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n738: \n739: ## Requirements\n740: \n741: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n742: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n743: \n744: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n745: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n746: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n747: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n748: \n749: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n750: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n751: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n752: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n753: \n754: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n755: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n756: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n757: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n758: \n759: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n760: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n761: \n762: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n763: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n764: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n765: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n766: \n767: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n768: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n769: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n770: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n771: \n772: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n773: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n774: \n775: #### Scenario: Context manager\n776: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n777: - **WHEN** the block exits\n778: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n779: \n780: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n781: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n782: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n783: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n784: \n785: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n786: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n787: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n788: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n789: \n790: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n791: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n792: \n793: #### Scenario: Create session\n794: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n795: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n796: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n797: \n798: #### Scenario: Delete session\n799: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n800: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n801: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n802: \n803: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n804: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n805: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n806: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n807: \n808: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n809: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n810: \n811: #### Scenario: Execute command\n812: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n813: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n814: \n815: #### Scenario: Files API\n816: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n817: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n818: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n819: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n820: \n821: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n822: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n823: \n824: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n825: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n826: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n827: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n828: \n829: ### Requirement: Session header management\n830: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n831: \n832: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n833: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n834: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n835: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n836: \n837: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n838: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n839: \n840: #### Scenario: Command failure\n841: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n842: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n843: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n844: \n845: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n846: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n847: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n848: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n849: \n850: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n851: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n852: \n853: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n854: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n855: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n856: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n857: \n858: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n859: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n860: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n861: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n862: \n863: ---\n864: \n865: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n866: \n867: \n868: Include: purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives considered.\n\n(End of file - total 868 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write proposal.md for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\nModule: integrations\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\nRelevant specs:\n--- integrations/design.md ---\n# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin — file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775891867064,"end":1775891867083}}}}
