{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891934978,"sessionID":"ses_28498b584ffeqx648sCyueA5sT","part":{"id":"prt_d7b686e65001umkorElV2Z4yFQ","messageID":"msg_d7b67660c0012EZOIb8232nO2k","sessionID":"ses_28498b584ffeqx648sCyueA5sT","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-eaf8567c4d8247638d3433cdc1989351","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nIntegrate AgentCube's code interpreter capabilities into Dify's plugin ecosystem, enabling Dify users to leverage AgentCube's sandboxed code execution environment directly within their AI workflows. This integration provides:\n\n1. **Seamless Dify Integration** — A Dify-compatible plugin that exposes AgentCube's Code Interpreter as a tool callable from Dify agent workflows\n2. **Reference Implementation** — A PCAP analyzer example demonstrating real-world usage of AgentCube SDK with LangChain/LangGraph agents in Kubernetes\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n#### Dify Plugin Package (`integrations/dify-plugin/`)\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest with metadata, resource permissions, and runner configuration |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider descriptor with identity and tool list |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` with credential validation |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema (router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session controls) |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` implementation delegating to AgentCube SDK |\n| `main.py` | Plugin entrypoint running `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `requirements.txt` | Dependency pins: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`, `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n| Documentation | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` |\n\n#### PCAP Analyzer Example (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI service with LangChain/LangGraph agents for PCAP analysis |\n| `Dockerfile` | Container image using `uv` with vendored `agentcube` SDK |\n| `deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes Deployment with secrets and resource limits |\n| `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, LangChain stack, AgentCube dependencies |\n\n#### Python SDK Dependencies\n\nThe integration depends on the existing `agentcube-sdk` providing:\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` — Session management and code execution via Control Plane + Router\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` — Agent runtime invocation\n- Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Modifications to the AgentCube control plane or router\n- New AgentCube SDK features (uses existing SDK `>=0.0.10`)\n- Dify platform changes (integrates with existing Dify plugin framework)\n- OAuth authentication flows (commented out in provider, not required for MVP)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### User Impact\n\n| User Type | Impact |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Dify Users | Gain access to AgentCube's sandboxed code execution without leaving Dify workflows. Can execute Python/JavaScript/TypeScript code, run shell commands, and manage sessions. |\n| Platform Operators | Single deployment artifact (Dify plugin package) to install. PCAP analyzer example provides reference for building custom AgentCube-powered agents. |\n| Developers | Clear API surface via tool parameters. SDK handles session lifecycle, retry logic, and error propagation. |\n\n### Technical Impact\n\n| Area | Impact |\n|------|--------|\n| **Architecture** | Adds a thin adapter layer between Dify's plugin interface and AgentCube SDK. No changes to AgentCube core. |\n| **Dependencies** | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` (Dify framework), `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` (AgentCube client) |\n| **Deployment** | Plugin packaged as Dify-compatible bundle; PCAP analyzer deployed as K8s workload |\n| **Testing** | Unit tests for tool/provider classes; integration tests against mock AgentCube endpoints |\n| **Security** | Credentials validated at provider level; sessions isolated per `session_id`; Router handles JWT auth |\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Dify plugin API changes | Medium | High | Pin `dify-plugin` to `<0.5.0`; monitor upstream releases |\n| AgentCube SDK breaking changes | Low | High | Pin `agentcube-sdk` version; SDK has stable public API |\n| Session leak in long-running workflows | Medium | Medium | Context manager ensures cleanup; explicit `stop()` on exit |\n| Timeout during long code execution | Medium | Low | Configurable per-call timeout; default 120s; PicoD timeout handling |\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- **No breaking changes** to existing AgentCube SDK\n- Plugin uses existing `CodeInterpreterClient` API surface\n- PCAP analyzer is a new example, no existing users affected\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct API Integration (No Plugin)\n\n**Description:** Dify users call AgentCube Router endpoints directly via custom HTTP tool.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No plugin development overhead; maximum flexibility |\n| Cons | Users handle session lifecycle manually; no credential management; no schema validation |\n| Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Poor UX; shifts complexity to end users |\n\n### Alternative 2: LangChain Tool Wrapper\n\n**Description:** Build a LangChain tool instead of Dify plugin, usable in LangChain-based Dify agents.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Broader LangChain ecosystem support; already used in PCAP analyzer |\n| Cons | Dify-native plugins have better integration (UI configuration, credential management); LangChain tool requires custom agent setup |\n| Verdict | ⚠️ Partial — Include as secondary option; Dify plugin is primary interface |\n\n### Alternative 3: Multiple Tools (Execute, Upload, Download)\n\n**Description:** Split code interpreter into separate tools: `execute_code`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Finer-grained control in Dify workflows; simpler per-tool schema |\n| Cons | Session management across tools is complex; Dify tool selection overhead for simple use cases |\n| Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Single unified tool with optional parameters is more ergonomic |\n\n### Alternative 4: Stateless Execution (No Session Reuse)\n\n**Description:** Each tool invocation creates a fresh sandbox, executes, and destroys it.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler mental model; no session state |\n| Cons | No persistent file system; higher latency per call; wasteful sandbox creation |\n| Verdict | ❌ Rejected — Session reuse is a key AgentCube feature; users can disable via `session_reuse=False` |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Core Plugin (MVP)\n\n- Implement plugin manifest, provider, and tool YAMLs\n- Implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider._validate_credentials`\n- Implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool.execute` with code/command execution\n- Add unit tests with mocked SDK\n- Write `README.md` and `GUIDE.md`\n\n### Phase 2: Session Management\n\n- Implement `session_id` and `session_reuse` logic\n- Add integration tests against real AgentCube endpoints (optional CI flag)\n- Handle edge cases: session creation failure, timeout, cleanup\n\n### Phase 3: PCAP Analyzer Example\n\n- Validate `pcap_analyzer.py` against AgentCube deployment\n- Update `Dockerfile` and `deployment.yaml` for production readiness\n- Add end-to-end test with sample PCAP file\n\n### Phase 4: Documentation & Polish\n\n- Complete `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`\n- Add troubleshooting guide for common errors\n- Performance benchmark and timeout tuning\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. **Functional** — Dify users can configure and invoke AgentCube Code Interpreter tool from workflows\n2. **Reliable** — Session cleanup occurs on context exit; no leaked sandbox resources\n3. **Observable** — Errors surface as `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` or `ToolInvokeMessage` JSON with actionable messages\n4. **Documented** — Plugin includes multilingual labels (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR) and comprehensive README\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version Constraint | Source |\n|------------|-------------------|--------|\n| `dify-plugin` | `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | PyPI |\n| `agentcube-sdk` | `>=0.0.10` | AgentCube monorepo |\n| `requests` | (via agentcube-sdk) | PyPI |\n| `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` (via agentcube-sdk) | PyPI |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `integrations/design.md` — Detailed file maps and code structures\n- `integrations/spec.md` — Formal requirements and scenarios\n- `python-sdk/design.md` — AgentCube SDK architecture\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` — SDK API contracts"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775891934967,"end":1775891934975}}}}
